Appendix: Custom CSS
/* custom-styles.css */
.reveal h1, .reveal h2 {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
}

/* Scrollable content for long slides */
.scrollable {
  height: 600px;
  overflow-y: auto;
  padding: 20px;
}

/* Better background handling */
.reveal .slides section[data-background] {
  color: white;
}

.reveal .slides section[data-background] h1,
.reveal .slides section[data-background] h2,
.reveal .slides section[data-background] h3 {
  color: white;
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
}

/* Timeline styling */
.timeline {
  border-left: 3px solid #667eea;
  padding-left: 20px;
  margin: 20px 0;
}

/* Table styling */
.reveal table {
  font-size: 0.8em;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  width: 100%;
}

.reveal table th,
.reveal table td {
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  padding: 8px;
  text-align: left;
}

.reveal table th {
  background-color: #667eea;
  color: white;
}

/* Code block styling */
.reveal pre {
  font-size: 0.7em;
  line-height: 1.2em;
}

.reveal code {
  background: #2d2d2d;
  color: #f8f8f2;
  padding: 2px 6px;
  border-radius: 3px;
}

/* Better column spacing */
.reveal .columns {
  display: flex;
  gap: 20px;
  align-items: flex-start;
}

/* Incremental list styling */
.reveal .incremental li {
  margin: 10px 0;
}

/* Fragment visibility fix */
.reveal .fragment {
  visibility: visible !important;
  opacity: 1 !important;
}

.reveal .fragment.visible {
  opacity: 1;
}

/* Center content properly */
.reveal .center {
  text-align: center;
}

/* Better slide padding for content-heavy slides */
.reveal .slides section {
  padding: 20px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Responsive font sizing */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .reveal .slides section {
    font-size: 0.8em;
  }
}

Appendix: Custom CSS
/* custom-styles.css */
.reveal h1, .reveal h2 {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  font-weight: 800;
}

/* Scrollable content */
.scrollable {
  height: 600px;
  overflow-y: auto;
  padding: 20px;
}

/* Background handling */
.reveal .slides section[data-background] {
  color: white;
}

.reveal .slides section[data-background] h1,
.reveal .slides section[data-background] h2,
.reveal .slides section[data-background] h3 {
  color: white;
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
}

/* Timeline styling */
.timeline {
  border-left: 3px solid #667eea;
  padding-left: 20px;
  margin: 20px 0;
  position: relative;
}

.timeline::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  left: -8px;
  top: 0;
  width: 12px;
  height: 12px;
  background: #667eea;
  border-radius: 50%;
}

/* Table styling */
.reveal table {
  font-size: 0.9em;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  width: 100%;
  margin: auto;
}

.reveal table th,
.reveal table td {
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  padding: 10px;
  text-align: left;
}

.reveal table th {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
  color: white;
  font-weight: 600;
}

.reveal table tr:hover td {
  background-color: rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.1);
}

/* Code block styling */
.reveal pre {
  font-size: 0.8em;
  line-height: 1.3em;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.2);
  border-radius: 8px;
}

.reveal code {
  background: #2d2d2d;
  color: #f8f8f2;
  padding: 3px 8px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

/* Column spacing */
.reveal .columns {
  display: flex;
  gap: 25px;
  align-items: flex-start;
}

/* Incremental lists */
.reveal .incremental li {
  margin: 12px 0;
}

/* Fragment animation */
.reveal .fragment {
  opacity: 0;
}

.reveal .fragment.visible {
  opacity: 1;
  transition: opacity 0.5s ease;
}

/* Center content */
.reveal .center {
  text-align: center;
}

/* Better padding */
.reveal .slides section {
  padding: 25px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Responsive sizing */
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  .reveal .slides section {
    font-size: 0.85em;
    padding: 15px;
  }

  .reveal .columns {
    flex-direction: column;
  }
}

/* Special text effects */
.text-gradient {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  font-weight: bold;
}

/* Notes styling */
.reveal .notes {
  font-style: italic;
  color: #666;
  font-size: 0.9em;
}

/* Emphasis box */
.emphasis-box {
  padding: 20px;
  margin: 20px 0;
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(102, 126, 234, 0.1) 0%, rgba(118, 75, 162, 0.1) 100%);
  border-left: 4px solid #667eea;
  border-radius: 8px;
}

/* Quote styling */
.reveal blockquote {
  border-left: 4px solid #667eea;
  padding-left: 20px;
  font-style: italic;
  color: #555;
  margin: 20px 0;
}

1. Fiscal consolidation
General prompt
‚ÄúTell me how Pakistan can reduce its fiscal deficit.‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Senior economic policy advisor&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Propose 3 fiscal consolidation measures that safeguard growth and the poor&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;High interest bill, low tax base, IMF targets, election constraints&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Measure: [action + fiscal yield]
- Implementation: [steps, timeline]
- Distributional impact: [winners/losers + mitigation]&lt;/output_format&gt;

2. Tax base broadening
General prompt
‚ÄúHow can we increase tax revenue?‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Tax policy specialist&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Identify the 3 highest-impact ways to broaden the tax base&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Under-taxed sectors (retail, real estate, agriculture), informality, weak enforcement&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Reform 1: [mechanism + expected yield]
- Admin changes: [data, audits]
- Risks & mitigation: [political, compliance]&lt;/output_format&gt;

3. Public debt sustainability
General prompt
‚ÄúWhat should be done about rising debt?‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Debt management expert&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Lay out a 3-pillar debt sustainability plan&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;High domestic rollover risk, external amortizations, interest rate path&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Pillar 1: [fiscal path]
- Pillar 2: [liability mgmt/reprofiling]
- Pillar 3: [growth & FX buffers]&lt;/output_format&gt;

4. Energy subsidies & circular debt
General prompt
‚ÄúFix the power sector problem.‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Energy economist&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Recommend 3 actions to unwind circular debt while protecting low-income users&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Tariff structure, line losses, SOE arrears, targeted cash transfers&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Action: [what + fiscal/operational impact]
- Targeting: [who/how]
- Timeline & KPIs&lt;/output_format&gt;

5. SOE reform
General prompt
‚ÄúWhat‚Äôs the best way to reform SOEs?‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Public enterprise reform advisor&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Design a triage plan for SOEs: privatize, restructure, or retain&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Financial losses, governance gaps, strategic vs commercial SOEs&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Triage criteria: [metrics]
- Track A/B/C: [policy for each]
- Governance fixes: [boards, audits, incentives]&lt;/output_format&gt;

6. Public investment (PSDP) efficiency
General prompt
‚ÄúHow do we improve development spending?‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Public investment management (PIM) specialist&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Prioritize and sequence projects to maximize economic return&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;PSDP pipeline overruns, fragmented funding, weak ex-ante appraisal&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Prioritization rules: [IRR, readiness]
- Portfolio actions: [drop/defer/fast-track]
- Monitoring: [stage-gates, KPIs]&lt;/output_format&gt;

7. Inflation & policy mix
General prompt
‚ÄúAdvise on inflation control.‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Macro policy advisor&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Recommend a fiscal-monetary-FX policy mix to lower inflation&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Food/energy shocks, exchange rate pass-through, indexation&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Fiscal: [measures + inflation impact]
- Monetary: [stance + transmission]
- FX/Trade: [buffers, import policy]&lt;/output_format&gt;

8. Exchange rate management
General prompt
‚ÄúWhat‚Äôs the right exchange rate policy?‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;External sector economist&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Outline the preferred exchange rate regime and operational guidelines&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Thin FX market, remittances, export competitiveness, reserves&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Regime choice: [rationale]
- Intervention rules: [when/how]
- Safeguards: [buffers, transparency]&lt;/output_format&gt;

9. Export diversification & industrial policy
General prompt
‚ÄúHow can we boost exports?‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Trade & industrial policy expert&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Propose 3 interventions to accelerate export diversification&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Textile concentration, logistics costs, standards compliance, SEZ potential&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Intervention: [constraint solved]
- Instrument: [credit, standards, zones]
- KPI: [export value/variety]&lt;/output_format&gt;

10. Agriculture prices & food security
General prompt
‚ÄúStabilize food prices.‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Agricultural economist&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Design a price-stability package without large fiscal costs&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;MSP design, buffer stocks, import timing, climate risk&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Tool 1: [how it stabilizes]
- Tool 2: [trade/logistics]
- Tool 3: [climate adaptation] + Risks&lt;/output_format&gt;

11. Social protection targeting
General prompt
‚ÄúImprove social safety nets.‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Social protection economist&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Strengthen targeting and shock-responsiveness of cash transfers&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Proxy means tests, dynamic registries, inflation spikes, disasters&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Targeting upgrade: [data/method]
- Shock trigger: [rules + funding]
- Leakage/coverage KPIs&lt;/output_format&gt;

12. Health financing
General prompt
‚ÄúMake health spending more effective.‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Health economist&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Recommend 3 financing reforms to improve outcomes per rupee&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Primary care gaps, catastrophic OOP spending, insurer/provider mix&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Reform: [payment model/benefit design]
- Expected outcome: [access/quality]
- Fiscal cost & savings&lt;/output_format&gt;

13. Education spending to learning
General prompt
‚ÄúIncrease education quality.‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Education economist&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Reallocate education budgets toward high-return learning interventions&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Teacher absenteeism, early-grade literacy, performance grants&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Reallocation 1/2/3: [from ‚Üí to + evidence]
- Accountability: [metrics]
- Timeline&lt;/output_format&gt;

14. Fiscal decentralization
General prompt
‚ÄúShould we decentralize more?‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Intergovernmental fiscal expert&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Design a fiscal decentralization package aligned with service delivery&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Assignment of functions, transfers, local revenue powers&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Function map: [who does what]
- Transfer formula: [criteria]
- Local revenue: [instruments + safeguards]&lt;/output_format&gt;

15. Climate finance & carbon pricing
General prompt
‚ÄúHow do we fund climate action?‚Äù
Structured prompt (right way)
&lt;role&gt;Climate finance economist&lt;/role&gt;
&lt;task&gt;Propose a financing mix and phased carbon pricing roadmap&lt;/task&gt;
&lt;context&gt;Adaptation needs, MDB financing, competitiveness concerns&lt;/context&gt;
&lt;output_format&gt;- Financing mix: [domestic + external]
- Carbon price path: [levels, timing]
- Offsets/CBAM readiness&lt;/output_format&gt;

